\subsection{2-Selmer rank}
\begin{definition}\label{g2c.two_selmer_rank}
\uses{ag.abelian_variety,ag.mordell_weil,ag.selmer_group,ag.tate_shafarevich,g2c.torsion}
The **2-Selmer rank** of an {{KNOWL('ag.abelian_variety', 'abelian variety')}} is the rank of its {{KNOWL('ag.selmer_group', '2-Selmer group')}}.

The difference between the 2-Selmer rank and the 2-rank of the {{KNOWL('g2c.torsion', 'torsion subgroup')}} is an upper bound on the rank of the {{KNOWL("ag.mordell_weil", "Mordell-Weil group")}}.  This bound is tight if and only if the 2-part of the {{KNOWL('ag.tate_shafarevich','Tate-Shafarevich group')}} is trivial
\end{definition}


